{"cursor":"15707","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox military conflict |conflict=Battle of Badon |partof=the Anglo-Saxon\nsettlement of Britain |date=Unknown, circa 500 |place=Unknown, various locations\npossible |coordinates = |casus=Saxons seeking to continue westward expansion\n|territory= |result=Strategic British victory; Saxon expansion halted for many\ndecades |combatant1=Britons |combatant2=Anglo-Saxons |commander1=Unknown,\npossibly King Arthur |commander2=Unknown |strength1=Unknown\n|strength2=Unknown |casualties1=Unknown |casualties2=Unknown,\napparently heavy }}\n\nThe 'Battle of Badon' (, ), also known as the 'Battle of Badon Hill' or 'Mount\nBadon' (; Modern ), is a battle thought to have occurred between a force of\nBritons and an Anglo-Saxon war band in the late 5th or early 6th\ncentury. Ashe, Geoffrey, From Caesar to Arthur pp.295-8 Chiefly known\ntoday for the supposed involvement of King Arthur, it is credited in medieval\nBritish and Welsh sources as a major political and military event but seems to\nhave passed unremarked in the Anglo-Saxon histories. Because of the limited\nnumber of sources, there is no certainty about the date, location, or details of\nthe fighting. Dupuy, R. Ernest & al. The Harper Encyclopedia of Military\nHistory From 3500 B.C. to the Present, 4th ed., p. 193. HarperCollins Pub. (New\nYork), 1993. Hollister, C. Warren. The Making of England to 1399, 8th\ned., p. 31. Houghton Mifflin Co. (New York), 2001.\n","linknr":340,"url":"Battle_of_Mons_Badonicus","recorded":1375088133,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Battle_of_Badon&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Battle_of_Badon&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Battle_of_Badon","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.D